ure generations may know and understand the basis of their redemption. For this reason Peter wrote his) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0841  Tc 0.9241  Tw (Second Epistle, in which he said) Tj132.48 0  TD -0.101  Tc 0.5457  Tw (: \223So I will always remind you of these things, even though you know them and are ) Tj-132.48 -11.52  TD -0.0825  Tc 0.5348  Tw (firmly established in the truth you now have. I think it is right to refresh your memory as long as I live in the tent of ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0768  Tc 1.3968  Tw (this body, because I know that I will soon put it as) Tj214.08 0  TD -0.0809  Tc 0.8866  Tw (ide, as our Lord Jesus Christ has made clear to me. And I will ) Tj-214.08 -11.52  TD -0.0988  Tc 1.2212  Tw (make every effort to see that after my departure you will always be able to remember these things.\224) Tj411.84 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (700) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0868  Tc 0.6868  Tw ( If we write ) Tj-421.92 -11.52  TD -0.0787  Tc 0.8448  Tw (down what we say, our words will live even after we are gone. ) Tj262.08 0  TD -0.0675  Tc 0.7275  Tw (Moses realized the importance of the written Word ) Tj-262.08 -11.52  TD -0.0673  Tc 0.2673  Tw (over the transience of our experiences. The written Word of God is the key to our salvation. For this reason Abraham ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0729  Tc 1.8729  Tw (said to the rich man in hell, who was concerned about the fate of his five brothers: \223The) Tj379.2 0  TD -0.179  Tc 1.499  Tw (y have Moses and the ) Tj-379.2 -11.52  TD -0.0823  Tc 0.5732  Tw (Prophets; let them listen to them\205. If they do not listen to Moses and the Prophets, they will not be convinced even ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0655  Tc -0.0545  Tw (if someone rises from the dead.\224) Tj128.64 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (701) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-102.72 -11.52  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.0326  Tc 0.3274  Tw (The Adam Clarke\222s Commentary) Tj134.88 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0326