watchword of all prophecy, and stands related to it as fundament) Tj274.08 0  TD -0.0801  Tc 1.3041  Tw (ally as the Decalogue to all laws, and the Lord ) Tj-274.08 -11.52  TD -0.1086  Tc -0.0114  Tw (Prayer to all prayers.\224 ) Tj88.32 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-52.32 -11.52  TD -0.1116  Tc 2.0182  Tw (The hymn opens with an appeal to the heavens and the earth. Moses had used similar words before in) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0883  Tc 0.5443  Tw (addressing the people but rather in the sense of calling upon heaven and earth to te) Tj333.6 0  TD -0.0913  Tc 0.3828  Tw (stify against a sinful nation. In the ) Tj-333.6 -11.52  TD -0.096  Tc 0.4103  Tw (first verses of this song, heaven and earth appear as less hostile witnesses. Earlier, Moses had said: \223I call heaven and ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0918  Tc 0.6918  Tw (earth as witnesses against you this day that you will quickly perish from the land that you are ) Tj382.08 0  TD -0.05  Tc 0.41  Tw (crossing the Jordan to ) Tj-382.08 -11.52  TD -0.0623  Tc 0.815  Tw (possess. You will not live there long but will certainly be destroyed.\224) Tj283.68 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (846) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.1062  Tc 0.4129  Tw ( And: \223Assemble before me all the elders of ) Tj-293.76 -11.52  TD -0.0905  Tc 0.6905  Tw (your tribes and all your officials, so that I can speak these words in their hearing and call heaven and e) Tj416.64 0  TD -0.0551  Tc 0.0951  Tw (arth to testify ) Tj-416.64 -11.52  TD -0.1132  Tc 0.4732  Tw (against them.\224) Tj57.12 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (847) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.1161  Tc 0.4533  Tw ( In this hymn a poetical parallel is drawn between the heavens and earth as listeners in vs. 1 and \223the ) Tj-67.2 -11.52  TD -0.0927  Tc 1.3327  Tw (rain [that] descends like dew,\205 like showers on new grass, like abundant rain on tender plants.\224 There is not) Tj453.12 0  TD -0.1606  Tc 0.0406  Tw (hing ) Tj-453.12 